ophy, and law. Nine timely essays explore our pivotal moment in history, from the question of reparations for slavery to the from the art—and impact—of the public apology.The editors of this volume encourage us to not only examine the roots of mistrust, but also to imagine a collective way forward, particularly as we face the continuing threat of the COVID-19 pandemic. Reconciliation and Repair provides thought-provoking perspectives in an age where they are desperately needed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aReparations for historical injusticesvCongresses. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh1 aBeerbohm, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeerbohm, Eric, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrooks, Roy L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHendrix, Burke A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJagmohan, Desmond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLu, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMinow, Martha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohamed, Saira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurphy, Colleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPreston-Roedder, Ryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRadzik, Linda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwartzberg, Melissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwartzberg, Melissa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook pa